\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 2. A. cruentus} L., {\i Syst. Nat.} ed. 10,{\i  2:} 1269 (1759) (incl.{\i  A. paniculatus} L., {\i A. patulus} Bertol.). Like {\b 1} but the terminal inflorescence usually dense and with short branches at the base; bracteoles 2-4 mm, with short mucro, 1-1½ times as long as the perianth. 2n = 34.{\i  Commonly naturalized, mainly in S. & C. Europe}. [Al Bl Bu Co Cr Cz Ga Ge He Hs Hu It Ju Lu Rm Rs(C, W, K) Sa Si.] ({\i Tropical and subtropical America.})
\par

