\pard\f0\fs28 Grown as a grain crop in Central America, but long cultivated for ornament in Europe, where red- or yellow-flowered plants have been known as {\i A. paniculatus} L.,{\i  Sp. Pl}. ed. 2, 1406 (1763).
\par

